BEGIN_PGML

[@ image( "21-R-WE-ZA-32.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

The thin rectangular plate [`D`] of mass [`m_D=[$md]\:kg`] is attached to two links [`AO`] and [`BC`] of lengths [`l_{AO}=[$lo]\:m`] and [`l_{BC}=[$lc]\:m`] that are both connected to pins.
When [`\theta=45^{\circ}`] link [`AO`] is moving with an angular velocity of [`\omega_{AO}=[$omegao0]\:rad/s`] in the direction shown, and a moment of [`M_{OA}=[$M]{\theta} N{\cdot}m`] is applied to it. If link [`AO`]
has a mass of [`m_{AO}=[$moa]\:kg`] and link [`BC`] has a mass of [`m_{BC}=[$mcb]\:kg`], find the angular velocity of link [`BC`] when [`\theta=90^{\circ}`]. Assume that the plate remains horizontal.
The following dimensions are known: [`r=[$r]\:m`], [`s=[$s]\:m`].

[`omega_{BC} = `][_____]{"$omegac"}[`rad/s`]

END_PGML

